     <body>
     <div type="encomium">
   <head>To my Friend M<seg rend="sup">r</seg>. Charles Allen.</head>
   <l>
      <hi>CHarles,</hi> by the muse <hi>Edward</hi> the <hi>Blacke</hi> seems faire,</l>
   <l>The daring Sonne of an vndaunted Sire.</l>
   <l>Liue not my hopes, if I can iudge more rare</l>
   <l>Their Acts, or thy expression. To require</l>
   <l>An equall censure, this with truth accords,</l>
   <l>They giue thee matter, thou afford'st them words.</l>
   <closer>
      <signed>John Lewis.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
